»CL9:               The Competitions
»CL8:               ----------------

»CL0:We'll of course arrange competitions at the party,
You're invited to compete in music, graphics and demos.
To make things easier for us, we've set up a really simple
rules which you'll have to follow in order to compete.

These Rules are valid all the competitors. Nothing can have
been released earlier, and the competitive programms must be
100% finished, we can't judge a demo or anything else for
waht it might become. Also the contestant must be present at 
the party.



























»CL9:Amiga Demo Competition:
»CL8:---------------------

»CL0: In the demo competition every coder can compete with
 two demos. The Demo must be able to run on Amiga. 
 (A4000/060-ppc & gfxcard) filesize max 4MB.

»CL9:C-64 Demo Competition:
»CL8:----------------------

»CL1: - »CL0:All groups can compete with as many demos as they wish.
»CL1: - »CL0:Mulitpart demos requires fast-loader.


Please consider if your demo is good enough before you decide
to join the competition. It is though to watch 20 demos created
using RSI demomaker, for many hours, so keep away the lame intros!























»CL9:Amiga Music Competition
»CL8:-----------------------

»CL0: In The music-competition every musician are
 allowed to compete with a maximum of two songs,
 and the song(s) must be given to us as a 
 non Soundtracker based format. 

 music should be created using any kind of 'exotic' musiceditor. 
 but no standard Tracker (e.g. Stonetracker, Protracker, Digibooster, 
 Octamed, Soundtracker, Startrekker, Art of Noise(Chorus), 
 Noisetracker, Quadracomposer)
 and no complete samples (no mp3, wav, 8svx, etc.).



























»CL9:C-64 Music Competition
»CL8:----------------------
 
»CL0: Maximum 2 songs per musician/group can compete.

 music should be created using any kind of 'exotic' musiceditor. 
 but no standard Tracker (e.g. Stonetracker, Protracker, Digibooster, 
 Octamed, Soundtracker, Startrekker, Art of Noise(Chorus),
 Noisetracker, Quadracomposer)
 and no complete samples (no mp3, wav, 8svx, etc.).

»CL9:OnStage Competitons:
»CL8:--------------------

»CL0: (e.g. Protracker-30min. Fast Competition)

























